**To find newly added mpath* disk .. need to compare output of mpath -ll & pvs. if a disk is available in mpath but not in pv then that will be the newly added disk.

05  multipath -ll | grep mpath
#newly created mpath ID will show like below
#mpatha 360xxx2ef
#pvs

#pvcreate /dev/mapper/mpatha
#pvs
 #vgcreate cauimdb /dev/mapper/mpatha
 # vgs
# lvcreate -L +1024G -n dccrmbkplv DCCRMBKPVG
# lvs
# mkfs.ext3 /dev/DCCRMBKPVG/dccrmbkplv
# mkdir /DCCRMBKP
# mount /dev/DCCRMBKPVG/dccrmbkplv /DCCRMBKP/

945  vgextend vg-app1 /dev/mapper/mpath4
