---vmware disk addition---
always add separate disk as extendind existing disk may result in fatal.
#fdisk -l		**it will show the new disk name, whether it is new or old check with #pvs command as it will show previously created pv.
then
# pvcreate /dev/sdf  **sdf is new disk not shown in pvs.
now check with #pvs 
then
# vgs   **which vg we will extend**
#vgextend datavg /dev/sdf
#vgs
#lvextend -L +50G /dev/mapper/datavg/lvname
#resize2fs /dev/mapper/datavg/lvname
